HEADWORD: Predigestion
<hw>Pre`di*ges"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Digestion too soon performed; hasty digestion.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Artificial digestion of food for
use in illness or impaired digestion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Predilect</ent>⟦br⟧
